title: Toufik Benamokrane
text:
Toufik Benamokrane (born March 22, 1980 in <a href="Souk%20El-Thenine">Souk El-Thenine</a>, <a href="B%C3%A9ja%C3%AFa%20Province">Béjaïa Province</a>) is an Algerian former <a href="association%20football">football</a> player. He played for the <a href="AS%20Khroub">AS Khroub</a> from 2011 to 2013, and retired at the end of the 2013 season.
Club career.
In 2007, Benamokrane joined <a href="MSP%20Batna">MSP Batna</a> after spending one season with <a href="JSM%20B%C3%A9ja%C3%AFa">JSM Béjaïa</a>. In April 2010, Benamokrane was kicked off the team by team president Messaoud Zidani.
In July 2010, Toufik Benamokrane joined the <a href="MC%20El%20Eulma">MC El Eulma</a> for a year. In July 2011, he is transferred to the <a href="AS%20Khroub">AS Khroub</a>, where he retired in July 2013.
